HEADWORD: Agraphia
<hw>A*graph"i*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'a</grk> priv. + <?/ to write.]</ety> <def>The absence or loss of
the power of expressing ideas by written signs. It is one form of
aphasia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

